page.title: 07CLAW PARK HOUSING ESTATE
page.content: {Claw Park}was built in{1953}and is a{housing estate.}Claw Park is also a{Cul De Sac}which is French for,'a road that doesn't lead anywhere.'There are ten{garages}in Claw Park. The houses in Claw Park are all{Council {houses. The maximum}number of rooms in the houses are{five,}three up, two down. Most of the{people}in Claw Park are{retired.}Nearly every body in Claw Park has moved in from other{areas. } There are about{6 children}who live in Claw Park. These children attend either{Clawton Primary School}or {Holsworthy Community College.}
